urch. The name derives, via Latin, from Greek <i>petros</i> ‘stone, rock’. This is used as a translation of the Aramaic byname <i>Cephas</i>, given to the apostle  Simon  son of Jona, to distinguish him from another of the same name (  Simon Zelotes ). ‘When Jesus beheld him, he said, Thou art Simon the son of Jona: thou shalt be called Cephas, which is by interpretation, A stone’ (John 1:42). According to Matthew 16:17–18, Christ says more explicitly, ‘Blessed art thou, Simon Bar-jona … thou art Peter, and upon this rock I will build my church’. The name has been in continuous use since the Middle Ages."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Gilles Ier Egidius de Chimay was born in 1130, in Chimay, Hainaut, Belgium, his father, Allard de Chimay, was 33 and his mother, Ida de Coucy, was 25. He married Adelheid de Rosoy in 1155. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1189, at the age of 59."},"et":{"1130–1189":"1130–1189","1128–Female":"1128–Surnud","1135–Female":"1135–Surnud","1160–1220":"1160–1220","1098–Male":"1098–Surnud","1105–1157":"1105–1157","1128":"1128","1105":"1105","1157":"1157","1135":"1135","1189":"1189","1155":"1155","1220":"1220","1098":"1098","1130":"1130","1160":"1160","Chimay,France.":"Prantsusmaa","Chimay, Hainaut, Belgique":"Chimay, Hainaut, Belgia","Orbais, Perwez, Brabant wallon, Belgique":"Orbais, Perwez, Brabant wallon, Belgia"},"fi":{"1130–1189":"1130–1189","1128–Female":"1128–Kuollut","1135–Female":"1135–Kuollut","1160–1220":"1160–1220","1098–Male":"1098–Kuollut","1105–1157":"1105–1157","1128":"1128","1105":"1105","1157":"1157","1135":"1135","1189":"1189","1155":"1155","1220":"1220","1098":"1098","1130":"1130","1160":"1160","Chimay,France.":"Ranska","Chimay, Hainaut, Belgique":"Chimay, Hainaut, Belgia","Orbais, Perwez, Brabant wallon, Belgique":"Orbais, Perwez, Brabant wallon, Belgia"},"fr":{"1130–1189":"1130–1189","1128–Female":"1128–Décédée","1135–Female":"1135–Décédée","1160–1220":"1160–1220","1098–Male":"1098–Décédé","1105–1157":"1105–1